Why is it that when a VN vet is portrayed (he or she) has <br>
character flaws?  Why aren't those of us that got on with <br>
our lives ever recognized positively?   Why does the press and society want us to be victims and sociopaths, that fly off the handle for little or no reason?  We are all not dressed in our fatigues and living in the streets as homeless crazies that can't keep a job or relationship. Many of us were able to resume a somewhat normal life and be successfull at what we are doing.  We are even part of this information age society.  <br>
